crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This script is a `Makefile` designed to interface with the `sphinx-build` documentation generation tool. It initializes variables for the Sphinx executable path, source directory, and output build directory. It defines a target that executes `sphinx-build` with the `-M help` option to display available Sphinx commands. A generic pattern rule is also present, which captures any unspecified `make` target and passes it as a mode argument to `sphinx-build`, enabling execution of various Sphinx build modes (e.g., HTML, LaTeX) via `make`.
